cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with weakly supervised semantic segmentation and object localization, which are tasks related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel training scheme that involves deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of inference and feedback, which are techniques related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions salient region detection and object location prediction, which are tasks related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
